 Bombay Tenancy and Agricultural Lands Act, 1948, Section 32. scope of-Legal effects of (i) a will executed by the landlord in his life time after the tenant became the "deemed purchaser" and hence the land-owner on 1.4.1957 and (ii) the proceedings taken on The basis of the will including mutation of the name of the legatee, postponement of sales under Sections 32F and 32G, entertainment of the suit by the Tenancy Aval Karkoon filed under Sections 14 and 29 of the Art, the dispossession. Of the deemed purchaser and the further sale by the recorded owner.
